Package: DeconmiR
Title: Cell Type Deconvolution using miRNA Expression Profliling
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given  = "Zhen",
             family = "Yang",
             email  = "zhenyang@fudan.edu.cn",
             role   = c("aut", "cre")),
      person(given  = "Andrew E.",
             family = "Teschendorff",
             email  = "andrew@picb.ac.cn",
             role   = c("aut")))
Description: DeconmiR is a R package to for the cell type deconvolution of 
      heterogeneous tissues representing a mixture of such cell-types based on 
      miRNA-seq data or microarray expression profiles. Right now, the package 
      can be used on miRNA expression of whole blood and breast tissue. This 
      package provides a unified testing interface to rapidly run multiple 
      state-of-the-art deconvolution methods. 
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports: MASS, e1071, quadprog, nnls, limma, ggplot2, reshape2
